The paper discusses security services such as authentication, confidentiality, privacy, access control, and integrity, which are all related to computer security. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the use of cloud computing, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses data and resource provenance, which is related to databases and falls under cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the use of blockchain technology, which is related to software engineering and falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses privacy, which is related to cybersecurity and falls under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
